author: HelloFresh
time required: 15 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 830 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 76 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 760 mg
course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
servings: 2
---

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, half the
@white wine vinegar{2.5%tsp}, ½ tsp @sugar{1%tsp}, ½ tsp
water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Microwave until shallot is
slightly softened, ~{30-40%seconds}.

Drain pickled shallot, reserving pickling liquid in bowl (you'll
use it in Step 4).

> Use 1 tsp sugar and 1 tsp water for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz}; using a #spatula{},
press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on
bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season with @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch},
and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
cooked through, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.

While pork cooks, massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{1} in
package to break up. Partially open package and insert
@butter{1%tbsp}. Microwave according to package instructions,
~{90%seconds}. Fluff with a #fork{}.

> To make it easier to fluff the rice, transfer to a bowl first.

In a large #bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz},
@mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, remaining vinegar, and @sugar{½%tsp}. Taste
and season with salt and pepper.

Add @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp} and @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz} to bowl
with reserved pickling liquid; stir to combine.

Divide rice and coleslaw between bowls. Top rice with pork and
pickled shallot. Drizzle bowls with sweet chili BBQ sauce and serve.